cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on device-free localization using radio frequency network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new model based on diffraction theory to explain the relationship between RSS loss and the position of the target, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses particle filtering tracing to recursively estimate the position of the target, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves the use of radio sensors to track the target, which can be considered as a multimedia application. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly mention any security-related aspects, but the use of device-free localization can have potential security implications, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security.
